All good advice except:<br>
<br>
&quot;Never keep gate mem'd first off.&quot;<br>
<br>
That's an opinion, not a fact. It is shared by many clerics I know, but not by all, and frankly (and controversially) I think it is a daft viewpoint, but there you go. For clerics below planar levels, it is bad bad advice, IMHO. I kept Gate loaded 100% of the time up to level 46, and still have it loaded 75% of the time now. It saved my character's life so many times I cannot count. I would have died on most of those occasions, pointlessly, had I not had it loaded (very rarely is it actually possible to load it in time if it is not loaded, whatever some might say).<br>
<br>
You don't need to DA and load Gate and then cast it in those multitude of situations that occur that require this IF you keep the darn spell loaded in the first place.<br>
<br>
Gate = lifesaver. Consider when to load it. Consider when to use it. Use your own judgement, each and every one of you. But don't follow blind rote that some advise to *never* load it. This at least is my advice, based on considerable experience. There are too many clerics who don't know how to play the darned class as it is, and this kind of thing is not helping.<br>
<br>
And I stress, I am *NOT* talking about raiding in big guild raids. I am talking about what most players do most of the time ... single or part groups in xp gathering places, often with at least some strangers.<br>
<br>
None of this detracts from the otherwise good advice on this thread. <p>--------------------------------------<BR><BR>
