Lanys T'vyl</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uulaian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ulaian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I live here.... get out.</span><br> <font color=#000033>(9/17/01 8:15:24 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How to gate when in alot of trouble.</span><hr size=1> I by far prefer having DA/DB up as opposed to gate. Have all 3 up at the same time is not an option, there simply isn't room in my spell lineup. If I do need to gate, I cast DA, then mem gate in the slot where I had DA, and cast as soon as DA wears off. Never failed me once. <br>
<br>
In my opinion, the slot where I might have gate memmed is much better used to keep a root or a stun ready, as those will save me and my group much more often than gate. I have 3 spell slots always taken up by my heals, another 2 always taken by DA and DB, and I have 1 slot I use for swapping buffs and even the rare nuke or a second stun. <br>
<br>
So having gate memmed also would severely limit my versatility in groups, having only 1 slot left open for situational spells. Neither root or stun are effective if you need to sit and mem them first, whereas you can easily do that with gate. Basically, I don't feel safe without root and stun memmed, they can be such a great help at almost all times. <p>Ulaian Moonleaf <BR>
59th outrider of Tunare <BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uperplexcerebrum.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Perplex Cerebrum</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://images.honesty.com/imagedata/h/920/44/29204482.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t d00d!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(9/21/01 12:41:56 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://images.honesty.com/imagedata/h/920/44/29204481.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How to gate when in alot of trouble.</span><hr size=1> Little known fact about EQ world mechanics. Recovering your concentration when casting spells is based on channeling skill, but... the channeling itself is based entirely on the /loc. Unless you are being stunned with spells or bashed, you will channel through a pickup truck falling on your head as long as your /loc remains the same. The amount of damage you receive and the number of mobs that are beating on you are irrelevant. This is why the corner trick works, because mobs are unable to move you from your current /loc.<br>
<br>
